    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Since <code>String</code> <strong>IS-A</strong> <code>CharSequence</code>, you can pass a <code>String</code> wherever you need a <code>CharSequence</code>, or assign a <code>String</code> to a <code>CharSequence</code>:</p>\n<pre><code>CharSequence cs = &quot;string&quot;;\nString s = cs.toString();\nfoo(s); // prints &quot;string&quot;\n\npublic void foo(CharSequence cs) { \n  System.out.println(cs);\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>If you want to convert a <code>CharSequence</code> to a <code>String</code>, just use the <code>toString</code> method that must be implemented by every concrete implementation of <code>CharSequence</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1886487,
      "reputation" : 422691,
      "user_id" : 1705598,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 92,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/aTFoe.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "icza",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1705598/icza"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 81,
    "last_activity_date" : 1453894538,
    "last_edit_date" : 1453894538,
    "creation_date" : 1407330601,
    "answer_id" : 25161321,
    "question_id" : 1391970,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Straight answer:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String s = \"Hello World!\";\n\n// String =&gt; CharSequence conversion:\n\nCharSequence cs = s;  // String is already a CharSequence\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/CharSequence.html\"><code>CharSequence</code></a> is an interface, and the <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/String.html\"><code>String</code></a> class implements <code>CharSequence</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
