      "body" : "I had another similar error (in scala) trying to use the <code>String.replace</code> method with argument types <code>(Char)</code>, but it needs two arguments, so I added the empty String as the second argument (which I assumed was the default) and converted the first argument to String (since it needed to match either both <code>Char</code> or <code>CharSequence</code>. So, mine was another example of closely reading the argument type options vs. my own method call."
