    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>That's a good question! You may get into troubles if you invoke API that uses generics and want to assign or return that result with a different subtype of the generic type. Java 8 helps to transform:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>    List&lt;String&gt; input = new LinkedList&lt;&gt;(Arrays.asList(&quot;a&quot;, &quot;b&quot;, &quot;c&quot;));\n    List&lt;CharSequence&gt; result;\n    \n//    result = input; // &lt;-- Type mismatch: cannot convert from List&lt;String&gt; to List&lt;CharSequence&gt;\n    result = input.stream().collect(Collectors.toList());\n    \n    System.out.println(result);\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
